article.headline: San Diego 74, Florida A&amp,M 64
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Brandon Johnson scored 23 points and became San Diego's all-time assists leader as the Toreros outlasted Florida A&M 74-64 Sunday night. Roberto Mafra and Chris Lewis each added 17 points for San Diego (7-9), and Matt Dorr had 10. Dale Hughes scored a team-high 17 points for the Rattlers (2-11), and Christopher Walker had 13. Johnson had seven assists to reach 468, surpassing David Fizdale, who had 465 from 1992-96. Mafra scored eight straight points for San Diego after Florida A&M had pulled to within 52-50 midway through the second half. The Toreros built a 40-21 lead with 3:26 left in the first half before the Rattlers closed the half on a 15-2 run, highlighted by a four-point play by Hughes with 3.2 seconds left.
